# Postiz daily-poster schedule (supercronic / standard 5-field cron).
# Times are in the container's TZ — set SCHEDULER_TZ in .env (default Etc/GMT+5).
# After editing:  make scheduler-restart
#
# Per-channel budgets, spread through the day. Each fire posts only what is
# actually ready and stops early when the backlog is empty ("nothing new"), so
# these lines are safe to leave running until everything is published.
#
#   LinkedIn — free, capped ~100 posts/24h by LinkedIn. 4 fires x 12 = 48/day,
#              comfortably under the cap even with manual runs on top.
#   X        — ~$0.20/post and it hard-blocked at 47 in one day. 2 fires x 5
#              = 10/day: cheap, and a third of the level that tripped the block.
#
# Raise/lower by editing the trailing number. Args are: <channel> <count>.
#
# min hour dom mon dow   command
0  6,11,16,21 * * *   /app/ops/scheduler/run-daily.sh linkedin 12 >> /app/data/daily.log 2>&1
30 8,20       * * *   /app/ops/scheduler/run-daily.sh x        5  >> /app/data/daily.log 2>&1
